body:
> Can async parsing apply highlights from a tree that's (slightly) out-of-date but not position edited?

It seems that's exactly the cause, based on the behavior I observe.

> then we either need an extra end_col check or make `nvim_buf_set_extmark()` slightly more forgiving for ephemeral marks?

I'm curious if an outdated coroutine should still be running after the state has changed? Wouldn't it be safer and more correct to cancel those?

UPD:
While this works, it feels a bit hacky.
```diff
--- a/src/nvim/api/extmark.c
+++ b/src/nvim/api/extmark.c
@@ -813,7 +813,7 @@ Integer nvim_buf_set_extmark(Buffer buffer, Integer ns_id, Integer line, Integer
       len = opts->ephemeral ? MAXCOL : ml_get_buf_len(buf, (linenr_T)line2 + 1);
     } else if (line2 == buf->b_ml.ml_line_count) {
       // We are trying to add an extmark past final newline
-      len = 0;
+      len = opts->ephemeral ? MAXCOL : 0;
     } else {
       // reuse len from before
       line2 = (int)line;
```
